The wonderful Russian philosopher Dmitry Galkovsky said it, but computer programmers, all those tech people called "software engineers", AI guys, robotics coders, etc. are the revolutionary class of the 21st century. They are what was called the "proletariat" in the 19th century.

This is why you see young men in positions of power. It's a technocratic revolution. AI guys won. They received their ideology and were already mature enough as a class to be receptive to it, achieved class consciousness, now they overthrew the system keeping them down. They won.

The name "DOGE" itself functions analogously to those early Soviet posters, the "ROSTA windows", that Mayakovsky used to produce. It's a nauseating meme picked intentionally to infuriate and humiliate the opponents of the technocrat faction, i.e. The Woke, bureaucrats, DEIs, etc.

Galkovsky talked about how the ROSTA window posters served as gang graffiti, the communists put them up to "mark" controlled territory. Weaponized ugliness to rub it into people's faces. Would be like if Musk printed out a bunch of "AI art" and plastered it everywhere in offices.
